<div class="modal fade keynote-details-modal" id="keynoteGopakumarModal" tabindex="-1"
    aria-labelledby="keynoteGopakumarTitle" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-centered modal-dialog-scrollable">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <div>
                    <span class="keynote-track">Power Electronics Keynote</span>
                    <h2 class="modal-title" id="keynoteGopakumarTitle">Prof. K. Gopakumar</h2>
                    <p>Indian Institute of Science, Bangalore</p>
                </div>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div class="keynote-modal-profile">
                    <img src="/images/keynote/kgopa3.jpg" alt="Prof. K. Gopakumar" loading="lazy" decoding="async"
                        width="500" height="484">
                    <div>
                        <h3>Multilevel Inverters for Drives Application Using Open-End Winding Configuration for Motor with Extended Linear Sinusoidal Modulation Control</h3>
                        <p>Recently, numerous interesting multilevel topologies have been reported for motor drive applications. However, the most popular topology to date remains the neutral point clamped (NPC) three-level topology, especially for medium-voltage drive applications.</p>
                        <p>This shows that industry is still looking for a viable alternative with reduced power-circuit complexity and an extended linear sinusoidal modulation range. Conventional inverter-fed drive schemes will have substantial low-order harmonics in the extended linear modulation range, also known as the overmodulation range. This lecture will focus on recent work from Prof. Gopakumar's lab on cascaded basic inverter topologies with reduced DC-link voltages and sinusoidal PWM operation in the extended linear modulation range.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="modal fade keynote-details-modal" id="keynoteSureshModal" tabindex="-1"
    aria-labelledby="keynoteSureshTitle" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-centered modal-dialog-scrollable">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <div>
                    <span class="keynote-track">Product Innovation Keynote</span>
                    <h2 class="modal-title" id="keynoteSureshTitle">Dr. Suresh Nair</h2>
                    <p>Founder and Managing Director, Amara Raja Design Alpha</p>
                </div>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div class="keynote-modal-profile">
                    <img src="/images/keynote/suresh_nair.jpeg" alt="Dr. Suresh Nair" loading="lazy"
                        decoding="async" width="1600" height="907">
                    <div>
                        <h3>Ignite: Sparking the Entrepreneur Within</h3>
                        <p>Startups and innovations have become buzzwords among youngsters over the last few years. Many millennials dream of building a startup of their own, and many organisations have been built to support such innovations through incubation.</p>
                        <p>There are a few success stories, but not many innovative products seem to have emerged in the recent past. This talk will examine the current state of affairs, the gaps that need to be bridged, and the importance of focusing on quality proposals over quantity. The session will showcase personal case studies, with special emphasis on the hardware product development life cycle.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="modal fade keynote-details-modal" id="keynoteSateeshModal" tabindex="-1"
    aria-labelledby="keynoteSateeshTitle" aria-hidden="true">
