        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <div>
                    <span class="keynote-track">Cybersecurity Keynote</span>
                    <h2 class="modal-title" id="keynoteSateeshTitle">Dr. Peddoju Sateesh Kumar</h2>
                    <p>Professor, IIT Roorkee</p>
                </div>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div class="keynote-modal-profile">
                    <img src="/images/keynote/sateesh_kumar.jpeg" alt="Dr. Peddoju Sateesh Kumar" loading="lazy"
                        decoding="async" width="412" height="412">
                    <div>
                        <h3>Beyond Signatures: Detecting Obfuscated and Zero-Day Malware</h3>
                        <p>Security breaches continue to pose significant threats to individuals, organizations, and critical infrastructure, and malware remains the primary weapon in modern cyberattacks. Adversaries increasingly leverage sophisticated tools and AI-assisted techniques to craft malicious payloads that evade existing defenses with fewer resources than ever before.</p>
                        <p>While AI and ML models have become integral to modern malware detection systems because they can identify complex patterns and detect previously unseen malware, they remain vulnerable to adversarial manipulation. This talk presents novel detection models that go beyond conventional malware detection to specifically target advanced obfuscation techniques, including code injection, metamorphism, packing, and zero-day malware.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

